des:
SuperConn offers the most comprehensive voice controlled smart home experience with Alexa. Control your home lighting and other devices hands free. Just say it, SuperConn will obey. 

Here’s a step by step guide:
(1). Download our "SuperConn" app in Google Play or iOS App Store;
(2). Launch the app and register a new account (or login if you’re already registered);
(3). Turn on SuperConn smart devices and connect them with “SuperConn” app;
(4). IMPORTANT: You can rename the devices with SuperConn App. So if you rename a smart bulb “bedroom light”, then Echo will get that same name after discovered the devices in Step 9;
(5). Download Amazon "Alexa" app from Amazon Market, Google Play or iOS App Store, and connect Echo with "Alexa" app;
(6). Search the Alexa Skills directory for "SuperConn";
(7). Click Enable skill of "SuperConn", then input your account username, password and region on the linking page;
(8). Talk to Echo "“Alexa,discover devices.”. Wait till Echo says "Discover is completed";
(9). Now all setup is done. Try talk to Echo to control your devices.

Here are the voice commands SuperConn has:

Lights:
* Alexa, turn on my bedroom light
* Alexa, turn off my bedroom light
* Alexa, dim my bedroom light
* Alexa, brighten my bedroom light
* Alexa, set the bedroom light to 20 percent

Plugs:
* Alexa, turn on my plug
* Alexa, turn off my plug

Currently this skill supports SuperConn smart plugs and smart bulbs. If you have any problems, please contact us at service@drens.com
